Remark that  if ${\mathcal G}$ is pro-$p$ free then ${\mathcal G}^{{\mathrm{ab}}} \simeq {\mathbb Z}_p^d$, where $d$ is the $p$-rank of ${\mathcal G}$.
This observation shows in particular that if  the group ${\mathcal G}$ corresponds to the Galois group of a pro-$p$ extension of number fields, then necessarily this extension is wildly ramified.

