We now explain how the Schur multiplier of ${\mathcal G}_S$ is related to the Leopoldt Conjecture.

\begin{prop}
Let $S$ be a set of places of ${\rm K}$, and for $v \in S$, let ${\mathcal U}_v$ be the pro-$p$ completion of the local units  at $v$. If the ${\mathbb Z}_p$-rank of the diagonal image of ${\mathcal O}_{\rm K}^\times$ in $\prod_{v\in S}{\mathcal U}_v$ is maximal, namely $r_1+r_2-1$, then $H^2({\mathcal G}_S,{\mathbb Q}_p/{\mathbb Z}_p)=0$. 
Moreover if $S_p \subseteq S$, these conditions are equivalent. In particular,  assuming the Leopoldt Conjecture for ${\rm K}$ at $p$,   ${\mathcal G}_{S_p}$ is free if and only if ${\mathcal T}_p$ is trivial.
\end{prop}

\begin{proof}
For the case of restricted ramification, see  \cite{maire}. For the general case, see \cite[Corollaire 1.5]{Nguyen}. 
\end{proof}

