\end{enumerate}


To produce such a situation, we realize $\Gamma$, along with its fixed-point-free automorphism, inside the maximal pro-$p$ extension ${\rm K}_{S_p}/{\rm K}$ of a $p$-rational field ${\rm K}$; in particular the condition $(i)$ will be automatically satisfied in our situation.

\begin{prop}\label{principle}
Suppose $\Gamma$ is a uniform pro-$p$ group and ${\rm L}$ is a Galois extension of a number field ${\rm K}$ such that ${\rm Gal}({\rm L}/{\rm K})$ is isomorphic to $\Gamma$ and the following conditions hold:
\begin{enumerate}
\item[$(i)$] there are only finitely many primes that are ramified in ${\rm L}/{\rm K}$;
\item[$(ii)$]  there exist infinitely many primes of ${\rm K}$
that split completely in ${\rm L}/{\rm K}$. 
\end{enumerate}
Then there exist $\Gamma$-extensions of number fields with arbitrarily large associated 
$\mu$-invariant.  
\end{prop} 


 \begin{proof}
 Since only finitely many primes of ${\mathbb Q}$ ramify in ${\rm K}$, a field of finite degree over ${\mathbb Q}$, the set $S_0$ of primes of ${\rm K}$ which split completely in ${\rm L}$ and are neither divisors of $p$ nor ramified over ${\mathbb Q}$ is infinite.  Fix a finite subset $S$ of $S_0$ of any prescribed order.  Let $\ell_1, \ldots, \ell_n$
be the residue characteristics of the primes in $S$.
 Let ${\rm F}/{\mathbb Q}$ a cyclic degree $p$ extension, described in Proposition \ref{ramsurQ}, which
  is ramified at each of these $\ell_i$. Then ${\rm L}{\rm F}/{\rm K}{\rm F}$ is Galois extension of group isomorphic to $\Gamma$. Put ${\rm K}_n={\rm L}^{\Gamma_n}$ and ${\rm F}_n:={\rm F}{\rm K}_n$.
  Then by applying Theorem \ref{theoriegenre} in ${\rm F}_n/{\rm K}_n$, one obtains

